         <abstract>
            <p>It is shown that the first positive zero $j_{\nu,1}$ of the Bessel function $J_\nu(x)$ is given by $$j_{\nu,1} = 2(\nu + 1)^{1/2}\bigg[1 + \frac{(\nu + 1)}{4} - \frac{7(\nu + 1)^2}{96} + \frac{49(\nu + 1)^3}{1152} - \frac{8363(\nu + 1)^4}{276480} + \cdots\bigg]$$ for $-1 &lt; \nu &lt; 0$.</p>
          </abstract>
